Glyph Menu

Press and hold on the menu button, then drag the mouse and
release when the label for the glyph you want is highlighted.

The choices are five sizes each of plusses, Xes, rectangles,
open circles and filled circles, as well as a single pixel
point.

You can set the glyph used by XGobi as a default glyph using
your resource file.  The default value is

*glyphType: 6
*glyphSize: 1

The glyph types are
 1 plus
 2 X
 3 open rectangle
 4 filled rectangle
 5 open circle
 6 filled circle
 7 point
and the sizes range from 1 to 5.

See the help file for the brushing I/O menu for information
about supplying point glyph, point color and line color
data in startup files.

